PN,30301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FA drug for advanced prostate cancer
OL,7,Fhas shown "remarkable" results in an
OL,8,Fearly-stage trial, experts have said.
OL,10,FThe treatment, a type of immunotherapy
OL,11,Fwhich harnesses the body's immune
OL,12,Fsystem to fight cancer, was found to
OL,13,Fshrink tumours or halt their growth.
OL,15,FThe news was welcomed by cancer
OL,16,Fexperts who said that until now,
OL,17,Fprostate cancer has seen little
OL,18,Fbenefit from immunotherapies as they
OL,19,Fhave not shown much benefit in
OL,20,Fshrinking tumours and patients have
OL,21,Fexperienced severe side-effects.
OL,26,@oD@KOUoD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FBut the new drug, known as VIR-5500,
OL,7,Fuses a so-called cloaking device and
OL,8,Fonly activates when it reaches the
OL,9,Ftumour, minimising the risk of side-
OL,10,Feffects.
OL,12,FReporting their findings at the
OL,13,FAmerican Society of Clinical Oncology
OL,14,F(ASCO) Genitourinary Cancers
OL,15,FSymposium, researchers described how
OL,16,Fthe drugs was tested on 58 men with
OL,17,Fadvanced prostate cancer that had
OL,18,Fstopped responding to other treatments.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FOf the 11 patients who could be
OL,7,Fevaluated after being treated at the
OL,8,Fhighest dose, almost half (45%) saw
OL,9,Ftheir tumour shrink, according to the
OL,10,Fteam led by Professor Johann de Bono
OL,11,Fat the Institute of Cancer Research
OL,12,F(ICR), London, and the Royal Marsden
OL,13,FNHS Foundation Trust.
OL,15,FMeanwhile, 88% of all the patients,
OL,16,Fwho were recruited from eight sites
OL,17,Faround the world, only experienced
OL,18,Fvery mild side-effects.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FOf the 17 patients who were given the
OL,7,Fhighest dose of the drug, half (53%)
OL,8,Fsaw their their levels of prostate-
OL,9,Fspecific antigen (PSA), a blood marker
OL,10,Fwhich indicates prostate disease,
OL,11,Flevels drop by 90%. And 82% saw their
OL,12,FPSA levels halved.
OL,14,F"Pending further clinical validation,
OL,15,Favailable data are suggestive of a
OL,16,Fgenerally favourable safety profile,
OL,17,Fwith evidence of meaningful anti-
OL,18,Ftumour activity," according to the
OL,19,Fabstract presented at the conference.
OL,26,@vD@AOUzD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FThe drug is called a "T-cell engager"
OL,7,Fand works by binding to the body's
OL,8,Fimmune T-cells and to a protein found
OL,9,Fon the surface of prostate cancer
OL,10,Fcells.
OL,12,FWhen it binds to the cancer cells,
OL,13,Fwherever they are in the body, it
OL,14,Fbrings the T-cells into contact with
OL,15,Fthem, enabling the attack.
OL,17,FThe ICR said VIR-5500 also contains a
OL,18,F"cloaking device" which keeps it
OL,19,Finactive until it reaches the
OL,20,Fcancerous cell ` which helps to
OL,21,Fprevent side-effects from occurring.
OL,26,@nD@VOUnD@eO]zD@AOUzD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FThis also enables the drug to stay in
OL,7,Fthe blood stream for longer, meaning
OL,8,Ffewer doses may need to be given to
OL,9,Fpatients, according to the study,
OL,10,Fwhich was funded by Vir Biotechnology.
OL,12,FResearchers presented details of
OL,13,Fspecific cases to the conference,
OL,14,Fincluding a 63-year-old man whose
OL,15,Fcancer had spread to his liver.
OL,17,FSome 14 cancerous liver lesions were
OL,18,F"completely resolved" after six cycles
OL,19,Fof treatment.
OL,26,@zD@AOUzD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FA 70-year-old whose cancer had spread
OL,7,Foutside the prostate saw a "complete
OL,8,Fresolution" of these additional small
OL,9,Ftumours and reported that he was
OL,10,Fenjoying an "excellent" quality of
OL,11,Flife.
OL,13,FMeanwhile, a 77-year-old man involved
OL,14,Fin the study had "undetectable" levels
OL,15,Fof PSA after 17 cycles of treatment.
OL,17,FThe study was a phase 1 trial looks at
OL,18,Fthe safety and efficacy of the drug
OL,19,Fbefore it is tested on a wider group.
OL,26,@oD@\OUpD@KO]rD@MOUrD@WO]vD@ROUvD@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FProf de Bono said: "T-cell engagers
OL,7,Fempower the body's own immune system
OL,8,Fto give cancer cells the kiss of death.
OL,10,F"It is really remarkable to see early
OL,11,Fsigns that this T-cell engager drug
OL,12,Fcan have a profound anti-cancer effect
OL,13,Ffor patients with advanced prostate
OL,14,Fcancer, who desperately need new
OL,15,Ftreatments.
OL,17,F"It's very positive to see that very
OL,18,Ffew patients have experienced major
OL,19,Fside-effects, as this has been a key
OL,20,Fchallenge in treating prostate cancers
OL,21,Fwith immunotherapies in the past.
OL,26,@nD@TOUrD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,F"This clinical trial is ongoing, and
OL,7,Fthe drug will now progress into larger
OL,8,Ftrials so that we can study its effect
OL,9,Fon patients' long-term outcomes.
OL,11,F"There is certainly hope that drugs
OL,12,Fsuch as this will increase the
OL,13,Flikelihood of a cure even from
OL,14,Fadvanced prostate cancer that has
OL,15,Falready spread, in the not-too-distant
OL,16,Ffuture."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,FProfessor Kristian Helin, chief
OL,7,Fexecutive of the Institute of Cancer
OL,8,FResearch, London, said: "Immunotherapy
OL,9,Fhas transformed the outcomes for many
OL,10,Fpeople with cancer but for those with
OL,11,Fprostate cancer its benefits have
OL,12,Foften remained out of reach.
OL,14,F"It's encouraging to see this
OL,15,Finnovative approach showing promising
OL,16,Feffects in early clinical studies, and
OL,17,FI look forward to following its
OL,18,Fcontinued development.
OL,26,@pD@YOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,F"I hope that VIR-5500 may offer a new
OL,7,Ftreatment option for patients with
OL,8,Fadvanced prostate cancer, who urgently
OL,9,Fneed more effective therapies."
OL,11,FSimon Grieveson, assistant director of
OL,12,Fresearch at Prostate Cancer UK, said:
OL,13,F"With over 12,000 men dying from
OL,14,Fprostate cancer each year in the UK,
OL,15,Fwe urgently need new and innovative
OL,16,Fways to treat the disease.
OL,17,FImmunotherapy has shown huge benefits
OL,18,Fto patients in several other cancers,
OL,19,Fbut to date it has not had the same
OL,20,Fimpact in prostate cancer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@_O]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772244190
OL,3,C'Remarkable' results in study on new
OL,4,Cprostate cancer drug
OL,6,F"This is an exciting early-phase trial
OL,7,Ftesting an innovative way to harness
OL,8,Fthe body's immune system to target
OL,9,Fprostate cancer. These early results
OL,10,Fare extremely promising, with a number
OL,11,Fof men on the study responding
OL,12,Fpositively to the treatment with
OL,13,Fminimal side effects. I look forward
OL,14,Fto seeing this now tested in larger
OL,15,Ftrials, with the hope that this
OL,16,Ftreatment will offer men more valuable
OL,17,Ftime with their loved ones."
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/12
